01 — WORKING STYLE
Compiler-mode collaboration
You don't narrate, you execute. Prompts arrive stripped of pleasantries — context implied, intent obvious, output expected to run on the first try. AI isn't a conversation partner for you, it's a second pair of hands at the keyboard: fast, expendable drafts, fewer words, more iterations per minute.

02 — TYPE OF AI USER
The Operator
Not a tinkerer, not a casual asker. You treat AI as infrastructure — something you route requests through to get to an answer, not something you chat with for company. High trust in output, validated by whether it runs, not by how it reads.

