04 — LEARNING & DECISIONS
Empirical, not encyclopedic
You learn by running the thing, not reading the manual. Decisions get made by testing the fastest path to a falsifiable result, then iterating — closer to a lab notebook than a strategy memo. Bias toward action over deliberation.

05 — WHAT MAKES YOU DIFFERENT
You don't chat. You compile.
Most users treat AI like a search engine with manners — long questions, polite framing, reading every word back. You treat it like a build tool: minimal input, maximal output, judged by whether it executes — not by whether it sounds smart.

06 — TO BECOME ELITE
